crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis:
The code begins by creating an empty string variable called OutputCom.

It then attempts to create an instance of the Windows Management Instrumentation (WMI) service with impersonation privileges. If successful, it queries the WMI service for all installed antivirus products.

The code then iterates through the list of installed antivirus products and checks if each product is enabled. If an antivirus product is enabled, its display name is added to the OutputCom string.

If no enabled antivirus products are found, the OutputCom string is set to "NOT_FOUND".

The code then checks if the OutputCom string contains the substring "indows". If it does, it creates a command string (windifcom) that uses the Windows command prompt to download a file from a remote URL and execute it.

If the OutputCom string does not contain the substring "indows", it creates a different command string (windifcom) that uses the Windows command prompt to download a file from a remote URL and save it to a temporary location, then execute it.

The code then creates an instance of the Windows Script Host (WSH) Shell object and executes the windifcom command.
